nodes.title: Do you want to use Detail Daemon here?

widgets_values: If you see a white mask above, then something was detected. Raise or lower the detection threshold as needed. (Yes, even down to 0.00001). Lowering it makes it more sensitive. 1 is the highest and basically makes it detect nothing.

nodes.title: Note: Detail Daemon
widgets_values: Bypassing Detail Daemon here will cause the workflow to stop working. Use the toggle switches above the KSampler and USDU nodes if you do not want to use Detail Daemon. Someone on youtube was using both of these at once. Seemed worth trying.
I just use Tile, but you have options here. There plenty of info out there on how ControlNet works. Just be aware using it does slow down the generation process.

nodes.title: Note: Load Image
widgets_values: You might have to put a random image into the load image node if you are not using this section. I know this has been a thing before and there is some way to workaround it, but putting an image there isn't the end of the world for me. Alternatively, you can delete this whole section.

nodes.title: Larger Guide and Max Size for Detailers
Note: Guide and Max Size
widgets_values:
If you Enable Larger Guide and Max Size, it will set the guide_size and max size settings to match the upscaled size from the first USDU node.

The default 512 / 1024 settings were probably meant for SD 1.5.

The problem with enabling this is that it definitely puts more load on your system and takes much longer, but is supposed to give a better result.

You'll have to play with the settings like denoise, steps, etc. to adjust (probably).

nodes.title: Do you want to use Detail Daemon here?
Do you want to use Detail Daemon here?
Note: CFG
widgets_values:
You can adjust the CFG to be higher or lower than the initial CFG here. I have found 2 to be a good number and just change the "op" setting to "add" or "sub". 

When using higher CFG, it is recommended to use less steps. With lower CFG, use higher steps. At least that is what I found via Google.

inputs.name: Larger Guide and Max Size for Detailers

widgets_values:
Two options for Detailers:

1. Slower: The usual 2 FaceDetailer nodes for Face>Eyes.

2. Faster: Detailer (SEGS) node as a combined detailer to detect and detail both at once. (note: this can be bugged on detection sometimes)

If you leave both enabled, only the Simpler Detailer's group output will be saved (probably).
This helps with the 2nd USDU having less artifacts usually. You can bypass this, but remember to change the upscale_by setting on the 2nd USDU or you will be going up to 4x.
I just use Tile, but you have options here. There plenty of info out there on how ControlNet works. Just be aware using it does slow down the generation process.

nodes.title: Note: Smoothed Energy Guidance
widgets_values: SEG will only be applied to the initial image. It bogs down the generation speed to much to have it go through USDU and beyond.

nodes.title: Note: Dynamic Thresholding
widgets_values:
Basically, the CFG min value should be set to whatever minimum value you want and vice versa for the CFG max value. Having too high of values here will cook your images.

Normally I just use Half Cosine Up for both modes, since a YouTube video about Dynamic Thresholding recommended that.

I have been getting some nice results using mimic_mode - Power up with various cfg_mode settings.

Definitely worth experimenting with.

One thing to note is the variability measure setting "AD" does not seem to work with scaling_startpoint setting "ZERO".

I'm not the authority on the settings for this node, so do as you like with it.
